Cascading stylesheet: look and formatting doc. Add style: color, font, height, width, background color...

<style>

h1, h2{

}

</style>
To apply more than one class, provide space : <h1 class="bold underline"></h1>
font-family: font type
size: px: pixel, %, em, keywords

css inheritance:

html -> head, body
body -> p, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5,

To underline: text-decoration: underline;

font-family: verdana, arial, genava, arial black; will load font as per order. if verdana not found, will load arial.

font-weight: bold, normal, lighter, bolder

external stylesheet: <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css" >
inline: <h1 style="color:red;font-size:25px;">
internal: <style></style>

text-decoration: underline, overline, text-through,none

font-style: italic, oblique, 

color: rgb(,,);
#ffcf79: hexcode value, can get after converting rgb to hex

font-size: % is relative unit of measure. If body has a font-size of 25px; and heading of 150% => h1 has font of 150% of 25px.
em: same as %: 1.2em means 1.2*25
xx-small, x-small, small, medium, large, x-large, xx-large

line-height: It is in em or %age. Relative to font-size.